## Context

Twelfth run — web search available. 8 projects all in development. Created 4 journal entries (#1345-1348) and 3 tasks (#931-933).

### Key findings recorded:
- **ts-drug-repurposing-network (journal #1345):** van Luik et al. (bioRxiv Jan 2026) — male-specific 5-HT2A receptor elevation in TS prefrontal cortex (BA10). Pimavanserin (FDA-approved) robustly reduced tics in mice via prefrontal mechanism. Prior pilot trial: 12% tic reduction, 70% subjective improvement. HIGH-PRIORITY repurposing candidate. Task #931 created.
- **ts-rare-variant-convergence (journal #1346):** Cadeddu et al. (Mol Psychiatry 2025) — Celsr3-deficient mice show D3 dopamine receptor upregulation in striosomal D1+ neurons. D3 antagonists reduce tics. Establishes rare-variant-to-receptor mechanism.
- **ts-neuroimmune-subtyping (journal #1347):** Three findings: (1) Sun & Bai immune dysregulation review (Frontiers Immunol Mar 2026) — three-pathway model (autoimmunity, neuroinflammation, gut-brain axis). Task #933. (2) TS PFC snRNA-seq (bioRxiv Jan 2026) — stress-related prefrontal activation. (3) Thalamo-frontal DBS+EEG (Mol Psychiatry) — alpha-band connectivity negatively correlates with severity.
- **Monitoring (journal #1348):** Comprehensive status update. Ecopipam NDA shifted to end of 2026 (delayed from Dec 2025).

### Tasks created:
- #931: research_director — evaluate pimavanserin + D3 antagonists for drug repurposing (P3)
- #932: research_director — integrate PFC snRNA-seq and DBS-EEG into CSTC atlas (P4)
- #933: research_director — evaluate three-pathway immune framework for subtyping (P4)

